<exercise>
  <ol>
    <li>
      For each of the following, decide whether the equation is linear or not. Justify your answer.
      <list type="enumerate">
        <li>
          <m>3x - 5y + 2z - 3 = 0</m>
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>-3xy + z = 2</m>
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>x - y = z</m>
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>x^{1/3} = y - z + 2</m>
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>\sin(x) = 0</m>
        </li>
      </list>
    </li>
    <li>
      Write each of the following linear systems as an equivalent augmented matrix:
      <ol>
        <li>
          <m>
            \begin{aligned}
              x + y &= 1 \\
              2x + y &= -4
            \end{aligned}
          </m>
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>
            \begin{aligned}
              2y + z &= 1 \\
              -2x + y &= -1 \\
              x &= 1
            \end{aligned}
          </m>
        </li>
    </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      Solve the following linear systems:
      <list type="enumerate">
        <li>
          <m>
            \begin{aligned}
              x + y &= 1 \\
              2x + y &= -4
            \end{aligned}
          </m>
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>
            \begin{aligned}
              2y + z &= 1 \\
              -2x + y &= -1 \\
              x &= 1
            \end{aligned}
          </m>
        </li>
      </list>
    </li>
    <li>
      Put the following matrices in RREF (or REF) and give the solution to the linear system.
      <ol>
        <li>
          <m>
            \begin{bmatrix}
              1 & 1 & 1 & 1 \\
              2 & 3 & 0 & 1 \\
              0 & -2 & 1 & 0
            \end{bmatrix}
          </m>
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>
            \begin{bmatrix}
              3 & 1 & 1 \\
              6 & 2 & 3
            \end{bmatrix}
          </m>
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>
            \begin{bmatrix}
              2 & 0 & 0 \\
              0 & 1 & 3
            \end{bmatrix}
          </m>
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>
            \begin{bmatrix}
              1 & 2 & 1 & 1 & 3 \\
              0 & 0 & 0 & 1 & 1 \\
              1 & 0 & 3 & 0 & 0 \\
              0 & 0 & 0 & 2 & 2
            \end{bmatrix}
          </m>
        </li>
    </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      Determine the values of <m>k</m> for which the following system has a solution:
      <ol>
        <li>
          <m>
            \begin{bmatrix}
              1 & -3 & 3 \\
              -2 & 6 & k
            \end{bmatrix}
          </m>
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>
            \begin{bmatrix}
              0 & 1 & 3 \\
              -2 & k & 0
            \end{bmatrix}
          </m>
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>
            \begin{bmatrix}
              1 & -1 & 1 \\
              0 & 6 & k \\
              0 & 0 & -1
            \end{bmatrix}
          </m>
        </li>
    </ol>
    </li>
</ol>
</exercise>